# Agent-loop instructions

You're working autonomously on a single GitHub issue in this repository. Read
this file fully, then read the issue with `gh issue view <N>`. Implement,
validate, refactor, and **create a local commit. Stop after the commit.** Do
not push, open a pull request, or invoke Gemini, Copilot, `reviewit`, or any
GitHub-hosted AI reviewer — the wrapper owns local Claude/Codex review,
fresh-base integration, publication, and PR creation.

> **Customize this file before running `/agent-loop`.** It was created from a
> starter template on first sync from upstream. Sections marked `TODO:` need
> values for your repo. The file lives at the repo root and is _not_ overwritten
> by subsequent syncs (its sync target uses `create_if_missing: true`).

